d%20at%20Meta%20and%20Google%20reveals%20which%20company%20is%20best%20for%20work-life%20balance%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20and%20Meta%20logos%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6632efed0dfb1341e9019316%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20product%20manage%20described%20the%20differences%20between%20working%20at%20Google%20and%20Meta%20based%20on%20his%20time%20at%20both%20companies.%3Cp%3ETayfun%20Coskun%20and%20Sebastien%20Bozon%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20product%20manager%20wrote%20a%20blog%20about%20his%20experiences%20working%20at%20Meta%20and%20Google.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBoth%20are%20great%20companies%20to%20work%20for%2C%20but%20Google%20employees%20may%20make%20less%20money%2C%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20the%20search%20giant%20may%20also%20provide%20better%20work-life%20balance%2C%20according%20to%20the%20PM's%20blog.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20the%20better%20company%20to%20work%20for%2C%20Meta%20or%20Google%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Meta%20product%20manager%20who%20also%20worked%20at%20Google%20in%20a%20similar%20role%20revealed%20some%20differences%20between%20the%20tech%20companies%20based%20on%20his%20experiences%20over%20the%20past%20six%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20McKinnon%20was%20a%20product%20manager%20at%20Meta%20between%202018%20and%202022.%20Afterward%2C%20he%20worked%20at%20Google%20for%20two%20years%20before%20returning%20to%20Meta%20in%20February%20to%20work%20on%20the%20company's%20Ray-Ban%20AI%20glasses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20verified%20his%20employment%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinnon%20wrote%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ddmckinnon.com%2F2024%2F04%2F26%2Fproduct-management-at-meta-vs-google-or-my-take-on-how-to-evaluate-your-googlemeta-offer%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20his%20personal%20blog%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20while%20the%20companies%20may%20seem%20similar%2C%20prospective%20candidates%20should%20know%20some%20key%20differences%20between%20the%20two%2C%20from%20work-life%20balance%20to%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMeta%20and%20Google%20are%20both%20phenomenal%20technology%20companies%20where%20great%20PMs%20can%20thrive%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinnon%20wrote%2C%20adding%20that%20if%20someone%20is%20looking%20for%20%26quot%3Bgrowth%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20stress%20and%20pressure%2C%20Meta%20is%20probably%20a%20better%20fit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20want%20to%20prioritize%20work-life%20balance%2C%20stability%2C%20and%20job%20security%2C%20Google%20could%20be%20a%20great%20place%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Meta%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20of%20the%20differences%2C%20according%20to%20McKinnon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompensation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20and%20Google%20offer%20product%20managers%20a%20salary%2C%20bonus%2C%20and%20Restricted%20Stock%20Unit%20(RSU)%20grants%20but%20have%20different%20pay%20structures%2C%20according%20to%20McKinnon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinnon%20wrote%20that%20Meta%20evenly%20distributes%20its%20RSUs%20over%20four%20years%2C%20while%20Google%20front-loads%20its%20grants%2C%20in%20which%2070%25%20of%20the%20stock%20is%20provided%20within%20the%20first%20two%20years%20of%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Btypical%20Google%20employee%26quot%3B%20may%20make%20less%20each%20year%20because%20the%20company%20offers%20much%20smaller%20stock%20refreshers%20than%20Meta%2C%20he%20wrote.%20Some%20companies%20provide%20stock%20refreshers%20%E2%80%94%20essentially%20more%20stock%20after%20the%20initial%20stock%20grant%20is%20provided%20%E2%80%94%20as%20an%20incentive%20for%20employees%20to%20stick%20with%20the%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRefreshers%20at%20Google%20are%20significantly%20smaller%20than%20Meta%20for%20the%20same%20level%20and%20role%20and%20performance%20multipliers%20are%20much%20scarcer%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinnon%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20McKinnon%2C%20at%20Google%2C%20employees%20can%20be%20rated%20to%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20impact%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20company%20but%20receive%20no%20additional%20bonus%20or%20stock%20refresher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20a%20Google%20spokesperson%20disputed%20McKinnon's%20assertion%20that%20employees%20make%20less%20each%20year%20partly%20because%20they%20aren't%20awarded%20additional%20bonuses%20or%20stock%20refreshers%20for%20having%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20impact%26quot%3B%20rating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20'Significant%20Impact'%20rating%20provides%20a%20generous%20multiplier%20for%20every%20employee%20who%20receives%20it%2C%20which%20boosts%20their%20bonus%20and%20equity%20refresh%20above%20the%20target%20amount.%20We%20know%20most%20Googlers%20are%20making%20a%20significant%20impact%2C%20and%20we%20want%20to%20reward%20them%20for%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bvast%20majority%20of%20Googlers%20received%20a%20compensation%20increase%26quot%3B%20in%202024%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eincluding%20a%20salary%20bump%2C%20equity%20grant%2C%20and%20bonuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20Google%20employees%20received%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employees-compensation-pay-salary-refreshers-equity-stock-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmaller%20compensation%20packages%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20employee%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20stock%20refreshers%20were%20%26quot%3Bnoticeably%20smaller%20than%20what%20Google%20has%20historically%20offered%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20a%20manager%20said%20some%20workers%20saw%20their%20total%20compensation%20drop%20despite%20receiving%20an%20%26quot%3Boutstanding%26quot%3B%20rating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EProject%20opportunities%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinnon%20describes%20Meta%20and%20Google%20as%20%26quot%3Bbottom-up%26quot%3B%20companies%2C%20where%20ideas%20largely%20originate%20from%20small%20teams%20building%20prototypes%20and%20other%20colleagues%20joining%20in%20if%20the%20prototype%20gains%20traction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoth%20Gmail%20(Google)%20and%20Marketplace%20(Meta)%20were%20famously%20side%20projects%20that%20grew%20into%20major%20components%20of%20the%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinnon%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20companies%20evaluate%20and%20support%20new%20ideas%20differently%2C%20McKinnon%20wrote%2C%20saying%20Meta's%20leadership%20can%20be%20enthusiastic%20about%20new%20projects%20and%20pursue%20them%20%26quot%3Baggressively%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20the%20idea%20can%20be%20quickly%20dropped%20if%20it%20does%20not%20meet%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20product%20manager%20recalled%20how%20he%20worked%20on%20an%20audio-social%20project%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-clubhouse-app%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClubhouse%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20audio-based%20social%20media%20app%2C%20was%20popular.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20couple%20hundred%20friends%20and%20I%20got%20invited%20to%20see%20if%20we%20could%20make%20social%20audio%20work%20in%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFacebook%20Blue%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%2C%20referring%20to%20Facebook's%20attempt%20at%20the%20time%20to%20make%20an%20audio-social%20app%20competitor.%20%26quot%3BLess%20than%20a%20year%20later%2C%20when%20it%20was%20clear%20we%20weren't%20meeting%20expectations%2C%20our%20team%20was%20blown%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20McKinnon%2C%20Meta's%20leadership%2C%20including%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%2C%20can%20also%20intervene%20if%20they%20find%20conflicting%20visions%20among%20teams%20for%20a%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Mark%20or%20his%20execs%20encounter%20two%20different%20visions%20for%20a%20product%2C%20they%20request%20reviews%20from%20the%20battling%20parties%20and%20make%20a%20call%20based%20on%20their%20judgment%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinnon%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThis%20top-down%20control%20can%20cut%20both%20ways%2C%20depending%20on%20which%20side%20of%20the%20decision%20you're%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Google%2C%20however%2C%20teams%20can%20work%20on%20similar%20projects%20for%20%26quot%3Bliterally%20decades%26quot%3B%20without%20leadership%20intervening%2C%20McKinnon%20wrote%2C%20pointing%20to%20Maps%20and%20Waze%2C%20GPS%20apps%20that%20are%20both%20owned%20by%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20be%20fruitful%20for%20product%20managers%20who%20want%20to%20pursue%20their%20visions%20for%20a%20product%20with%20their%20respective%20teams%20but%20also%20%26quot%3Bfrustrating%20for%20ambitious%20PMs%20who%20want%20to%20build%20products%20that%20require%20larger%20teams%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20project%20timelines%20can%20%26quot%3Bspan%20decades%26quot%3B%20at%20Google%2C%20according%20to%20McKinnon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20wrote%20that%20when%20he%20pitched%20an%20idea%20to%20a%20Google%20VP%2C%20the%20executive%20responded%20back%20that%20the%20idea%20was%20great%20but%20that%20he'd%20rather%20have%20employees%20focus%20on%20Google's%20search%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20interaction%20encapsulates%20how%20Google%20thinks%20about%20change%2C%20which%20is%20likely%20correct%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20Google%20shareholders%20but%20potentially%20not%20appealing%20to%20prospective%20product%20managers%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinnon%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Google%20spokesperson%20pointed%20to%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai's%20statements%20regarding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falphabet-issues-first-ever-dividend-beats-estimates-stock-buyback-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlphabet's%20first-quarter%20performance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20which%20the%20CEO%20explained%20how%20the%20company%20is%20trying%20to%20move%20faster%20by%20simplifying%20team%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompany%20transparency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20does%20maintain%20some%20of%20the%20transparency%20the%20company%20was%20known%20for%20in%20its%20earlier%20days%2C%20McKinnon%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Meta%2C%20McKinnon%20was%20aware%20of%20what%20other%20teams%20were%20working%20on%2C%20partly%20through%20the%20company's%20internal%20forums%20and%20dashboards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20also%20still%20hosts%20the%20weekly%20Q%26amp%3BA%20sessions%20with%20his%20employees%2C%20taking%20questions%20%26quot%3Boff%20the%20cuff%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinnon%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20upfront%20in%20their%20reports%20about%20promotions%20and%20employee%20ratings%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bcompensation%20is%20formulaic%20and%20predictable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20downside%20to%20the%20transparency%20is%20that%20employees%20have%20%26quot%3Bnowhere%20to%20hide%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20everyone%20knows%20what%20employees%20are%20working%20on%2C%20and%20people%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20%26quot%3Btake%20a%20back%20seat%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20McKinnon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Google%2C%20employees%20mostly%20communicate%20through%20email%20or%20chat%2C%20so%20it's%20more%20difficult%20to%20know%20what%20everyone%20is%20doing%2C%20McKinnon%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinnon%20also%20wrote%20that%20he%20felt%20Google%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20wasn't%20as%20candid%20with%20his%20answers%20to%20employees%20like%20Zuckerberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20wrote%20that%20compensation%20is%20also%20less%20predictable%2C%20and%20feedback%20from%20leadership%20is%20harder%20to%20obtain%20at%20the%20search%20giant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20this%20isn't%20great%20for%20those%20looking%20to%20learn%20and%20grow%2C%20this%20organizational%20style%20makes%20it%20much%20easier%20to%20let%20work%20drift%20into%20the%20background%20when%20other%20life%20priorities%20need%20your%20attention%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20transparency%20has%20declined%20for%20both%20companies%2C%20McKinnon%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Expression'%20in%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Meta%2C%20McKinnon%20feels%20that%20dissent%20is%20welcomed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMeta%20feels%20like%20a%20quasi-academic%2C%20truth-seeking%20organization%20where%20decisions%20are%20made%20with%20data%20and%20dissent%20is%20encouraged%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThis%20environment%20can%20be%20quite%20unsettling%20to%20those%20used%20to%20a%20more%20consensus-based%20or%20non-confrontational%20culture.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20is%20different%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20%26quot%3Bfree%20expression%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20employees%20are%20more%20%26quot%3Breserved%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20McKinnon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BQuestioning%20priorities%20is%20generally%20not%20encouraged%2C%20which%20does%20tend%20to%20make%20for%20a%20more%20collegial%20work%20environment%20but%20can%20be%20frustrating%20for%20PMs%20who%20want%20to%20effect%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgooglers-arrested-and-fired-israel-protest-project-nimbus-nyc-sunnyvale-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20fired%20at%20least%2028%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20protesting%20the%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproject-nimbus-google-sundar-pichai-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProject%20Nimbus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20%241.2%20billion%20cloud-computing%20contract%20with%20Israel's%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECareer%20ladder%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinnon%20wrote%20that%20the%20career%20ladder%20seems%20faster%20at%20Meta%20than%20at%20Google%2C%20where%20progression%20can%20often%20be%20based%20on%20seniority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinnon%20mentions%20that%20Meta's%20leadership%20is%20filled%20with%20young%20VPs%2C%20including%20the%20company's%20chief%20financial%20officer%2C%20Susan%20Li%2C%20who%20assumed%20the%20role%20when%20she%20was%2036.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoogle%20is%20much%20more%20time-based%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinnon%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20are%20given%20a%20quota%20for%20tenure-based%20promotions%2C%20and%20while%20promotions%20based%20on%20excellent%20performance%20can%20happen%2C%20they%20are%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20rarer%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20McKinnon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20a%20caveat%3A%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20these%20career%20progression%20observations%20cut%20both%20ways.%20I%20have%20never%20been%20in%20this%20situation%2C%20but%20I%20believe%20that%20it%20is%20much%20easier%20to%20get%20fired%20for%20poor%20performance%20at%20Meta%20than%20Google%2C%20which%20should%20certainly%20be%20a%20factor%20for%20those%20for%20whom%20job%20security%20is%20paramount.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPMs%20vs.%20Software%20Engineers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EProduct%20managers%20at%20Meta%20and%20Google%20can%20serve%20different%20purposes%2C%20according%20to%20McKinnon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Google%2C%20McKinnon%20saw%20that%20projects%20were%20largely%20created%20and%20led%20by%20software%20engineers%2C%20and%20PMs%20played%20a%20more%20auxiliary%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Meta%2C%20there's%20a%20stronger%20emphasis%20on%20product%20managers%20who%20are%20%26quot%3Bresponsible%20for%20both%20ensuring%20the%20broader%20team%20is%20building%20something%20useful%20and%20that%20usefulness%20can%20be%20quantified%20and%20iterated%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoth%20approaches%20have%20their%20merit%2C%20but%20I%20never%20could%20shake%20the%20feeling%20that%20Google%20could%20delete%20its%20entire%20PM%20function%20and%20not%20feel%20much%20in%20the%20way%20of%20repercussions%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinnon%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproduct-manager-work-culture-differences-between-meta-google-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714948530000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6632ef61ec0c6965690003a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproduct-manager-work-culture-differences-between-meta-google-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20product%20manager%20who%20worked%20for%20both%20Meta%20and%20Google%20reveals%20the%20companies'%20biggest%20cultural%20differences%20%E2%80%94%20and%20which%20is%20best%20for%20work-life%20balance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lloydlee%40insider.com%20(Lloyd%20Lee)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A53%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproduct-manager-work-culture-differences-between-meta-google-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Talks%20to%20collapse%3F%20Israel%20blames%20Hamas%2C%20says%20Rafah%20attack%20'soon'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714947943000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109865700%2Cimgsize-1408521.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Ftalks-to-collapse-israel-blames-hamas-says-rafah-attack-soon%2Farticleshow%2F109865648.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F109865648.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EIsraeli%20officials%20have%20not%20travelled%20to%20Cairo%20to%20take%20part%20in%20indirect%20diplomacy%2C%20but%20on%20Sunday%20Netanyahu%20re